      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i need help with this python function for my uni coding lab. the grader is super strict about the time limit and it keeps failing my submission because the complexity is too high for large inputs. can u optimize it so it passes the runtime tests? thanks.\n\n```python\ndef find_prime_factors(n):\n    factors = []\n    d = 2\n    temp = n\n    while temp > 1:\n        while temp % d == 0:\n            factors.append(d)\n            temp //= d\n        d += 1\n    return factors\n```",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The issue here is that the while loop is not optimized for large inputs. We can optimize it by using a more efficient algorithm and some mathematical properties of prime numbers. \n\n```python\ndef find_prime_factors(n):\n    factors = []\n    i = 2\n    while i * i <= n:\n        while n % i:\n            i += 1\n        n //= i\n        factors.append(i)\n    if n > 1:\n        factors.append(n)\n    return factors\n```\n\nThis optimized function works by only checking up to the square root of `n` because a larger factor of `n` would be a multiple of a smaller factor that has already been checked. This significantly reduces the time complexity from O(n) to O(sqrt(n)).",
